  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In this paper, we study the representations and <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msup><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>∗</mo></mrow></msup></math> -extensions of Novikov superalgebras. Many properties of a Novikov superalgebra can be lifted to its <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msup><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>∗</mo></mrow></msup></math> -extensions such as nilpotency, solvability and decomposition. In particular, we discuss the equivalence of <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msup><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>∗</mo></mrow></msup></math> -extensions. Moreover, we develop 1-parameter formal deformations theory of Novikov superalgebras.</subfield>
